  "prompt": "Is there something wrong with me if I don't find my wife physically attractive anymore?",
  "response": "It's not uncommon for physical attraction in relationships to ebb and flow over time. Changes in physical attraction can stem from a variety of factors, including shifts in emotional connection, lifestyle changes, or even individual health and stress levels. \n\nIt's important to reflect on the underlying reasons for this shift in attraction. Open communication with your spouse about your feelings can be beneficial. It might also be helpful to consider couples counseling or therapy to explore these feelings in a supportive environment. Sometimes, working through emotional and relational issues can rekindle physical attraction. \n\nRemember, relationships are multi-faceted, and physical attraction is just one aspect of a complex bond. Your feelings are valid, and taking steps to address them is a positive approach.",
